se of touch, muscle strength, flexibility, and posture, as well as the brain's role in avoiding falls.", "citations": {"08b29f61-ad72-46e6-859d-df2e6233ec1b_349742184": 90.0}}], "references": ["08b29f61-ad72-46e6-859d-df2e6233ec1b_349742184", "2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624", "80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165", "184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782", "cf35f7cc-4afe-4e57-aaa1-60eec2e0d061_430451653"]}
