e attributed to multiple factors, including diseases, medications, vision and hearing problems, and environmental factors, which can impact balance and increase the risk of falls.", "citations": {"08b29f61-ad72-46e6-859d-df2e6233ec1b_349742184": 80.0}}, {"text": "Falls in older adults are contributed to by various factors including disease, medication, vision and hearing impairments, physical function, health status, behavior, and environment, highlighting the importance of a comprehensive approach to fall prevention.", "citations": {"08b29f61-ad72-46e6-859d-df2e6233ec1b_349742184": 80.0}}, {"text": "Falls in older adults are caused by a combination of factors, including lack of muscle strength, poor balance, and health status, which can lead to serious injuries and loss of independence.", "citations": {"b2fbc30c-0aa3-4c9b-a45f-46cc57366767_74910826": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Exercises like Tai Chi, muscle strength and balance exercises, and functional training can help reduce fall risk in older adults by improving balance and mobility, with balance training being a key component of effective fall-prevention programs.\"", "citations": {"184485a7-25df-4efa-b2f3-f28ae72d25e3_199781782": 80.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi has been shown to reduce the risk of falls in older adults by improving their balance.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Tai Chi can help reduce fall risk in older adults by improving balance, mobility, and cognitive functioning, and can be beneficial for patients with Parkinson's and dementia.\"", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 80.0}}, {"text": "Scientific exercises, including Tai Chi and muscle strength and balance exercises, can help reduce the risk of falls in older adults by improving balance, muscle power, and endurance.", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Exercises like Tai Chi and Ba Duan Jin, which strengthen balance, muscle power, and endurance, can help reduce fall risk in older adults, and adapting the home environment can also play a crucial role in fall prevention.\"", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"Tai Chi and standing on one leg are recommended exercises for improving balance, with Tai Chi shown to reduce falls in older adults with balance problems.\"", "citations": {"eac7354a-8d3a-4125-a99c-ff8769c17923_331358921": 90.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is recommended for improving balance, with studies suggesting it reduces the risk of falls in older adults.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 80.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is beneficial for improving balance and mobility, especially for patients with Parkinson\u2019s and degenerative arthritis, as it contributes to better cognitive functioning and has a positive effect on movement disorders.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 80.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is a recommended exercise for improving balance and preventing falls in the elderly, as it strengthens functional exercise such as balance ability, muscle strength and endurance.", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 80.0}}, {"text": "Tai Chi is recommended as an exercise to improve balance, along with other strength and balance exercises like yoga.", "citations": {"08b29f61-ad72-46e6-859d-df2e6233ec1b_349742184": 80.0}}, {"text": "Adults over 65 experience falls annually, with one in three or every six people falling, and Tai Chi has been suggested to reduce this risk by improving balance.", "citations": {"2e864b6f-2e85-4876-845a-6831478b1237_437053624": 80.0}}, {"text": "\"More than 30% of adults over 65 experience falls annually, which is roughly equivalent to one in three or every 6 people.\"", "citations": {"07c8ac1c-33e7-4d1c-ad80-5b3ba6e77003_370105309": 80.0}}, {"text": "Falls occur in 1 in 6 people over 65 in Taiwan, according to the National Health Administration's analysis of the 2017 National Health Interview Survey.", "citations": {"f059ca9d-4aa0-4556-96f0-a43da6da33f7_830344688": 80.0}}, {"text": "Balance exercises, such as Tai Chi, should be practiced one to two times a week to improve balance.", "citations": {"eac7354a-8d3a-4125-a99c-ff8769c17923_331358921": 80.0}}, {"text": "Adequate lighting and removing tripping hazards can help prevent falls in older adults by creating a safer home environment.", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 80.0}}, {"text": "Adequate lighting and removing tripping hazards can help prevent falls in older adults by creating a safe environment.", "citations": {"80c8da15-5fa3-4f38-8fa6-3c8ddc7d04f2_904596165": 80.0}}, {"text": "Environmental factors, such as adequate lighting and removing tripping hazards, can help prevent falls in older adults by reducing the interaction of the person with their environment that may lead to falls.", "citations": {"cf35f7cc-4afe-4e57-aaa1-60eec2e0d061_430451653": 80.0}}, {"text": "Adequate lighting can help prevent falls in older adults by reducing tripping hazards and improving visibility.", "citations": {"cf35f7cc-4afe-4e57-aaa1-60eec2e0d061_430451653": 80.0}}, {"text": "Adequate lighting and removing tripping hazards can help prevent falls in older adults, in addition to regular exercise, routine physicals, and vision checkups.", "citations": {"cf35f7cc-4afe-4e57-aaa1-60eec2e0d061_430451653": 80.0}}, {"text": "Squatting is a resistance exercise that can help build up muscles, including those in the lower limbs, which can be beneficial for improving balance and reducing the risk of falls.", "citations": {"a3e8fc90-96ac-491a-9391-1d36b954f8e8_220672298": 80.0}}, {"text": "Exercises such as squatting, lunges, and stair climbing can help strengthen lower limb muscles, which is important for fall prevention, especially among the elderly.", "citations": {"b2fbc30c-0aa3-4c9b-a45f-46cc57366767_74910826": 80.0}}, {"text":