uantum computer.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "The US and China are the countries investing heavily in quantum computing, aiming to leverage its potential to transform various industries.", "citations": {"401cd12a-6c4c-4c7c-9ca3-dcf526538f39_398369350": 90.0}}, {"text": "China is a leading country in quantum computing development, with its 'Origin Wukong' quantum computer showing stable operation and attracting significant international attention.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "China is one of the countries investing in quantum computing, as evidenced by its development of the 'Origin Wukong' superconducting quantum computer.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "China is at the forefront of quantum computing development with its 'Origin Wukong' supercomputer, which has gained significant global attention and has been integrated into the country's 'four calculations in one' system.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "China is a leading country in quantum computing research, with its third-generation autonomous superconducting quantum computer \"Origin Wukong\" showing significant progress and investment in the field.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "Quantum computing has the potential to change various industries, including finance, biomedicine, and others, due to its great potential in artificial intelligence, biomedicine, financial analysis, and other fields.", "citations": {"76e3d61c-e991-43a2-8ebe-637114089506_116579795": 80.0}}, {"text": "Google achieved quantum supremacy using its Sycamore quantum processor, led by John Martinis, as reported at the end of 2019.", "citations": {"a43fd179-918c-4992-bba0-84a1fcb140c4_765885224": 100.0}}, {"text": "China is currently leading in state funding for quantum technologies,