 involved in Greenland's mineral development, with extensive licenses and a history of production in the region.", "citations": {"4ae7f149-1ea4-4da8-9d73-8f0641b266ca_887720299": 80.0}}, {"text": "Tanbreez Mining has been granted permission to extract rare earth minerals in Greenland, with production slated to begin in 2024, and the mine is estimated to contain over half of the world's rare earth resources.", "citations": {"95d6394d-1b2c-4be0-8d8e-36dc3c1cf662_711284580": 90.0}}, {"text": "Shenghe Resources Holding, a Chinese corporation, has expressed interest in Greenland's rare earth minerals through its subsidiary Greenland Minerals.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 80.0}}, {"text": "China and the United States are significant players in the Global Rare Earth Elements Market, with China dominating the market in terms of mining and processing volume.", "citations": {"cbf1d513-b13d-46cf-961f-a94c596437cc_781260089": 80.0}}, {"text": "The countries that are significant players in the Global Rare Earth Elements Market are the United States and China, with China being the world's leading supplier and hosting the majority of the world's reserve of rare earth minerals.", "citations": {"be0e1159-bd31-403e-acf1-b495b0455519_773343369": 80.0}}, {"text": "China and the United States are significant players in the Global Rare Earth Elements Market, with China having a quasi-monopoly on rare earths and permanent magnets.", "citations": {"be0e1159-bd31-403e-acf1-b495b0455519_773343369": 80.0}}, {"text": "China and the United States are significant players in the Global Rare Earth Elements Market, with China controlling a large majority of the production and trade of rare earth elements.", "citations": {"20cc6025-fb31-4659-a224-93409e805966_481091063": 80.0}}, {"text": "China and the United States are key players in the global rare earth elements market, with China being the largest supplier and the US increasing domestic production.", "citatio